{"title_page": "The Valleyfolk", "text_new": "\n\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = The Valleyfolk\n| italic_title             = no\n| image                    = Valleyfolk-logo.png\n| image_upright            = 0.9\n| caption                  = Day version of the logo\n| starring                 = [[Barats and Bereta|Joe Bereta]]<br /> [[Elliott Morgan]]<br /> [[Steve Zaragoza]] <br/> <br/> ''Formerly:'' <br/>[[Lee Newton]]\n| country                  = [[United States]]\n| location                 = [[Los Angeles]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2018|01|8}}\n| last_aired               = Present\n| website                  = https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCkEXXbo1QOTesV8h2hkN-1g\n| website_title            = The Valleyfolk on YouTube\n}}\n\n'''The Valleyfolk''' is a [[YouTube]]-based comedy group originating in [[Los Angeles]], California. The group was founded by former [[SourceFed]] hosts [[Barats and Bereta|Joe Bereta]], [[Elliott Morgan]], [[Lee Newton]], and [[Steve Zaragoza]]. The channel launched in January of 2018<ref name=\"TubeFilterLaunch\">[https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/01/08/the-valleyfolk-sourcefed-reunion/ Four Original SourceFed Hosts Reunite To Launch New Channel Called The Valleyfolk]</ref> and gained over 93,000 subscribers within the first 24 hours.<ref name=\"BiggestThing\">[https://vocal.media/geeks/why-the-valleyfolk-will-be-the-biggest-thing-on-youtube-in-2018/ Why The Valleyfolk Will Be the Biggest Thing on YouTube in 2018]</ref>\n\nThe group gained national attention in 2019 by appearing on the NBC comedy competition show ''[[Bring the Funny]]'',<ref>[https://www.nbc.com/bring-the-funny/credits/credit/season-1/the-valleyfolk/ The Valleyfolk: Bring the Funny Contestant]</ref><ref name=\"PasteMag\">[https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/07/nbc-bring-the-funny-preview.html Check Out a Hilarious Sketch in This Exclusive Clip from NBC's Bring the Funny]</ref> beating out thirty-nine other comedy acts and winning the show's inaugural season.<ref name=\"TubeFilterWin\">[https://www.tubefilter.com/2019/09/18/former-sourcefed-hosts-the-valleyfolk-win-first-season-of-nbcs-bring-the-funny/ TubeFilter - Former SourceFed Hosts \u2018The Valleyfolk\u2019 Win First Season Of NBC\u2019s \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019]</ref>\n\nAs of September 23rd, 2019, the group currently consists of Bereta, Morgan, and Zaragoza with founding member Newton being shockingly kicked out of the group five days after being heavily featured and winning Bring The Funny<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cc0pcIfhKq0&t=1s Lee Newton Announcement | The Valley Folk (Update)]</ref>\n\n==History==\n===Founding===\nThe four hosts first worked together at [[SourceFed]], beginning as the original hosts of the channel in 2012. The channel was created in conjunction with YouTube personality [[Philip DeFranco]] and [[YouTube]] itself. While Joe and Elliott left the channel in 2014, Lee left in 2015, and Steve reduced his role to part-time; the channel continued making news commentary and other comedic videos until its demise in March of 2017. Less than one year later, the group of four reunited independently and on January 8th, 2018, The Valleyfolk was born.<ref name=\"TubeFilterLaunch\" /><ref name=\"BiggestThing\" /><ref name=\"ANewBeginning\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2RsVpR_X5hE A New Beginning...]</ref><ref>[https://www.wetheunicorns.com/news/original-sourcefed-team-reunited-valleyfolk/ The Original SourceFed Team Have Reunited For An Awesome New Show]</ref> Due to the previous success of the four, both individually and together, the group gained more than 93,000 subscribers within the first 24 hours and more than 4,000 patrons within the first 48.<ref name=\"BiggestThing\" /><ref name=\"Unicorns\">[https://www.wetheunicorns.com/news/original-sourcefed-team-reunited-valleyfolk/ The Original SourceFed Team Have Reunited For An Awesome New Show]</ref>\n\nThe Valleyfolk logos, one featuring mountains at day and one featuring them at night, were created by David Morgan, graphic artist and brother of Elliott Morgan.<ref>[http://dav.idmorgan.com/the-valleyfolk-logo/ The Valleyfolk Logo]</ref>\n\n===''Bring the Funny''===\nOn July 9, 2018, the group announced that they were participating in NBC's comedy competition show ''[[Bring the Funny]]'',<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cEHfw2mm74o We Are on a Reality Show]</ref> appearing as part of the Sketch Act Division.<ref>[https://www.ibtimes.com/nbcs-bring-funny-premiere-meet-host-judges-contestants-2805363 NBC\u2019s \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019 Premiere: Meet The Host, Judges And Contestants]</ref><ref>[https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/06/meet-the-contestants-on-nbcs-bring-the-funny.html Meet the Contestants on NBC's Bring the Funny]</ref> The competition consists of four rounds and the prize is $250,000 and the opportunity to perform at the [[Just for Laughs]] comedy festival.<ref name=\"FutonCritic\">[http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/06/04/nbcs-new-competition-series-bring-the-funny-reveals-40-comedy-acts-set-to-vie-for-250000-prize-package-and-chance-to-perform-at-just-for-laughs-festival-386401/20190604nbc04/ NBC's New Competition Series \"Bring the Funny\" Reveals 40 Comedy Acts Set to Vie for $250,000 Prize Package and Chance to Perform at Just for Laughs Festival]</ref>\n\nIn the first round, or the Open Mic round, the Valleyfolk began their run with a sketch in which they played \"mole people\". The sketch elicited praise from [[Kenan Thompson]] for the commitment the quartet showed to the bit.<ref>[https://talentrecap.com/open-mic-nights-end-on-bring-the-funny-with-the-best-night-yet/ Open Mic Nights End On \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019 With The Best Night Yet]</ref> In the Comedy Clash round, the group went head to head with competing comedian Drennon Davis. Their sketch involved an inappropriately gleeful robot doctor informing a woman of her husband's demise.<ref>[https://talentrecap.com/did-bring-the-funny-chrissy-teigen-and-the-judges-get-it-right-this-week/ Did \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019s Chrissy Teigen And The Judges Get It Right This Week?]</ref> In the semifinals, the group performed a sketch that parodied a superhero academy that involved a flurry of feathers being dumped on the audience.<ref>[https://talentrecap.com/was-the-last-bring-the-funny-semifinal-the-best-episode-yet/ Was The Last \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019 Semifinal The Best Episode Yet?]</ref> The group made it to the final round of the competition by being selected as the viewer-voted wildcard team.<ref name=\"LAT_BtF_finale\">[https://www.latimes.com/socal/glendale-news-press/entertainment/story/2019-09-10/nbcs-bring-the-funny-taps-alex-theatre-to-round-out-season \"NBC's 'Bring the Funny' taps Alex Theatre to round out season\"]. ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''.</ref> On September 17, 2019, they won the show's first season by receiving the most votes from the viewing public. In addition to the prize money and [[Just for Laughs]] invite, the group's national television exposure has resulted in an estimated 10,000 new YouTube subscribers by the day after the show's finale.<ref name=\"TubeFilterWin\"/>\n\n===Other work===\nOn October 11, 2018, [[h3h3Productions]] made a video roasting Valleyfolk member Elliott Morgan's previous work on a pilot of a [[TLC (TV network)|TLC Network]] show titled <i>I Catfished My Kid</i>. In response, The Valleyfolk published their own video in response, garnering more than 200,000 views in two days.<ref name=\"DDRoast\">[https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/h3h3-elliott-morgan/ The Daily Dot: 2 YouTube channels unearth embarrassing old footage in hilarious roast battle]</ref>\n\nOn July 7, 2019, the Valleyfolk appeared as guests at the inaugural RTX Podcast Festival in [[Austin, Texas]]. Their podcast, <i>The Valleycast</i>, was one of six guest podcasts taped live at the annual [[RTX (event)|RTX]] event hosted by [[Rooster Teeth]].<ref name=\"Austin\">[https://www.austinchronicle.com/screens/2019-07-05/rooster-teeth-pumps-up-the-volume-with-new-podcasts-at-rtx-austin/ The Austin Chronicle: Rooster Teeth Pumps up the Volume With New Podcasts at RTX Austin]</ref>\n\n===Newton's Departure===\nOn November 1st, 2019, a video titled 'Lee Announcement | The Valleyfolk (Update)' was posted on the main channel.  In it, the group explained the absence of Newton from the past month of content as well as explained the future of the channel.  Fifteen minutes later, Newton posted her own video from her channel explaining that her last official date with the group was September 23rd, 2019 and that it was not her decision to leave the team.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mmuJ8QSh8Sg&t=1s Lee Newton - An Announcement]</ref> In the week following the announcement, the Valleyfolk channel lost 20,000 subscribers and over 700 patrons, prompting a follow-up video from the trio apologizing for their handling of the announcement.<ref name=\"reveal_firing_cc\">{{cite web |last1=McCarthy |first1=Shawn L. |title=The Valleyfolk reveals they fired Lee Newton after winning NBC\u2019s Bring The Funny |url=https://thecomicscomic.com/2019/11/07/the-valleyfolk-reveals-they-fired-lee-newton-after-winning-nbcs-bring-the-funny/ |website=The Comic's Comic}}</ref>\n\n==Recurring segments==\n*Your Show - a variety show that often involves sketches, games, and viewer questions.<ref name=\"TubeFilterYourShow\">[https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/07/11/the-valleyfolk-variety-series-your-show/ The Valleyfolk, SourceFed\u2019s Spiritual Successor, Launches Variety Series Titled \u2018Your Show\u2019]</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=57gqeKoLMj0 Our Baby Is Born]</ref>\n*Your World Today - a satirical news and current events show.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXz9498yucsQmTyqtwQU2ps5GzQNg4guh Your World Today]</ref>\n*The Valleycast - a weekly behind the scenes video podcast.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXz9498yucsSQ8InQAUmC1W9vVGK3XFfO The Valleycast Highlights]</ref>\n*Games\n**Trivia Bidet\n**Movie Movie Game\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Bring the Funny}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Valleyfolk, The}}\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:American comedy troupes]]\n[[Category:American podcasters]]\n[[Category:American sketch comedians]]\n[[Category:Bring the Funny contestants]]\n[[Category:Comedians from California]]\n[[Category:Comedy YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Performing groups established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Sketch comedy troupes]]\n[[Category:SourceFed people]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2018]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = The Valleyfolk\n| italic_title             = no\n| image                    = Valleyfolk-logo.png\n| image_upright            = 0.9\n| caption                  = Day version of the logo\n| starring                 = [[Barats and Bereta|Joe Bereta]]<br /> [[Elliott Morgan]]<br /> [[Steve Zaragoza]] <br/> <br/> ''Formerly:'' <br/>[[Lee Newton]]\n| country                  = [[United States]]\n| location                 = [[Los Angeles]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2018|01|8}}\n| last_aired               = Present\n| website                  = https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCkEXXbo1QOTesV8h2hkN-1g\n| website_title            = The Valleyfolk on YouTube\n}}\n\n'''The Valleyfolk''' is a [[YouTube]]-based comedy group originating in [[Los Angeles]], California. The group was founded by former [[SourceFed]] hosts [[Barats and Bereta|Joe Bereta]], [[Elliott Morgan]], [[Lee Newton]], and [[Steve Zaragoza]]. The channel launched in January of 2018<ref name=\"TubeFilterLaunch\">[https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/01/08/the-valleyfolk-sourcefed-reunion/ Four Original SourceFed Hosts Reunite To Launch New Channel Called The Valleyfolk]</ref> and gained over 93,000 subscribers within the first 24 hours.<ref name=\"BiggestThing\">[https://vocal.media/geeks/why-the-valleyfolk-will-be-the-biggest-thing-on-youtube-in-2018/ Why The Valleyfolk Will Be the Biggest Thing on YouTube in 2018]</ref>\n\nThe group gained national attention in 2019 by appearing on the NBC comedy competition show ''[[Bring the Funny]]'',<ref>[https://www.nbc.com/bring-the-funny/credits/credit/season-1/the-valleyfolk/ The Valleyfolk: Bring the Funny Contestant]</ref><ref name=\"PasteMag\">[https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/07/nbc-bring-the-funny-preview.html Check Out a Hilarious Sketch in This Exclusive Clip from NBC's Bring the Funny]</ref> beating out thirty-nine other comedy acts and winning the show's inaugural season.<ref name=\"TubeFilterWin\">[https://www.tubefilter.com/2019/09/18/former-sourcefed-hosts-the-valleyfolk-win-first-season-of-nbcs-bring-the-funny/ TubeFilter - Former SourceFed Hosts \u2018The Valleyfolk\u2019 Win First Season Of NBC\u2019s \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019]</ref>\n\nAs of September 23rd, 2019, the group currently consists of Bereta, Morgan, and Zaragoza with founding member Newton being ousted from the group in a unanimous decision by the other members.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cc0pcIfhKq0&t=1s Lee Newton Announcement | The Valley Folk (Update)]</ref>\n\n==History==\n===Founding===\nThe four hosts first worked together at [[SourceFed]], beginning as the original hosts of the channel in 2012. The channel was created in conjunction with YouTube personality [[Philip DeFranco]] and [[YouTube]] itself. While Joe and Elliott left the channel in 2014, Lee left in 2015, and Steve reduced his role to part-time; the channel continued making news commentary and other comedic videos until its demise in March of 2017. Less than one year later, the group of four reunited independently and on January 8th, 2018, The Valleyfolk was born.<ref name=\"TubeFilterLaunch\" /><ref name=\"BiggestThing\" /><ref name=\"ANewBeginning\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2RsVpR_X5hE A New Beginning...]</ref><ref>[https://www.wetheunicorns.com/news/original-sourcefed-team-reunited-valleyfolk/ The Original SourceFed Team Have Reunited For An Awesome New Show]</ref> Due to the previous success of the four, both individually and together, the group gained more than 93,000 subscribers within the first 24 hours and more than 4,000 patrons within the first 48.<ref name=\"BiggestThing\" /><ref name=\"Unicorns\">[https://www.wetheunicorns.com/news/original-sourcefed-team-reunited-valleyfolk/ The Original SourceFed Team Have Reunited For An Awesome New Show]</ref>\n\nThe Valleyfolk logos, one featuring mountains at day and one featuring them at night, were created by David Morgan, graphic artist and brother of Elliott Morgan.<ref>[http://dav.idmorgan.com/the-valleyfolk-logo/ The Valleyfolk Logo]</ref>\n\n===''Bring the Funny''===\nOn July 9, 2018, the group announced that they were participating in NBC's comedy competition show ''[[Bring the Funny]]'',<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cEHfw2mm74o We Are on a Reality Show]</ref> appearing as part of the Sketch Act Division.<ref>[https://www.ibtimes.com/nbcs-bring-funny-premiere-meet-host-judges-contestants-2805363 NBC\u2019s \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019 Premiere: Meet The Host, Judges And Contestants]</ref><ref>[https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/06/meet-the-contestants-on-nbcs-bring-the-funny.html Meet the Contestants on NBC's Bring the Funny]</ref> The competition consists of four rounds and the prize is $250,000 and the opportunity to perform at the [[Just for Laughs]] comedy festival.<ref name=\"FutonCritic\">[http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/06/04/nbcs-new-competition-series-bring-the-funny-reveals-40-comedy-acts-set-to-vie-for-250000-prize-package-and-chance-to-perform-at-just-for-laughs-festival-386401/20190604nbc04/ NBC's New Competition Series \"Bring the Funny\" Reveals 40 Comedy Acts Set to Vie for $250,000 Prize Package and Chance to Perform at Just for Laughs Festival]</ref>\n\nIn the first round, or the Open Mic round, the Valleyfolk began their run with a sketch in which they played \"mole people\". The sketch elicited praise from [[Kenan Thompson]] for the commitment the quartet showed to the bit.<ref>[https://talentrecap.com/open-mic-nights-end-on-bring-the-funny-with-the-best-night-yet/ Open Mic Nights End On \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019 With The Best Night Yet]</ref> In the Comedy Clash round, the group went head to head with competing comedian Drennon Davis. Their sketch involved an inappropriately gleeful robot doctor informing a woman of her husband's demise.<ref>[https://talentrecap.com/did-bring-the-funny-chrissy-teigen-and-the-judges-get-it-right-this-week/ Did \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019s Chrissy Teigen And The Judges Get It Right This Week?]</ref> In the semifinals, the group performed a sketch that parodied a superhero academy that involved a flurry of feathers being dumped on the audience.<ref>[https://talentrecap.com/was-the-last-bring-the-funny-semifinal-the-best-episode-yet/ Was The Last \u2018Bring The Funny\u2019 Semifinal The Best Episode Yet?]</ref> The group made it to the final round of the competition by being selected as the viewer-voted wildcard team.<ref name=\"LAT_BtF_finale\">[https://www.latimes.com/socal/glendale-news-press/entertainment/story/2019-09-10/nbcs-bring-the-funny-taps-alex-theatre-to-round-out-season \"NBC's 'Bring the Funny' taps Alex Theatre to round out season\"]. ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''.</ref> On September 17, 2019, they won the show's first season by receiving the most votes from the viewing public. In addition to the prize money and [[Just for Laughs]] invite, the group's national television exposure has resulted in an estimated 10,000 new YouTube subscribers by the day after the show's finale.<ref name=\"TubeFilterWin\"/>\n\n===Other work===\nOn October 11, 2018, [[h3h3Productions]] made a video roasting Valleyfolk member Elliott Morgan's previous work on a pilot of a [[TLC (TV network)|TLC Network]] show titled <i>I Catfished My Kid</i>. In response, The Valleyfolk published their own video in response, garnering more than 200,000 views in two days.<ref name=\"DDRoast\">[https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/h3h3-elliott-morgan/ The Daily Dot: 2 YouTube channels unearth embarrassing old footage in hilarious roast battle]</ref>\n\nOn July 7, 2019, the Valleyfolk appeared as guests at the inaugural RTX Podcast Festival in [[Austin, Texas]]. Their podcast, <i>The Valleycast</i>, was one of six guest podcasts taped live at the annual [[RTX (event)|RTX]] event hosted by [[Rooster Teeth]].<ref name=\"Austin\">[https://www.austinchronicle.com/screens/2019-07-05/rooster-teeth-pumps-up-the-volume-with-new-podcasts-at-rtx-austin/ The Austin Chronicle: Rooster Teeth Pumps up the Volume With New Podcasts at RTX Austin]</ref>\n\n===Newton's Departure===\nOn November 1st, 2019, a video titled 'Lee Announcement | The Valleyfolk (Update)' was posted on the main channel.  In it, the group explained the absence of Newton from the past month of content as well as explained the future of the channel.  Fifteen minutes later, Newton posted her own video from her channel explaining that her last official date with the group was September 23rd, 2019 and that it was not her decision to leave the team.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mmuJ8QSh8Sg&t=1s Lee Newton - An Announcement]</ref> In the week following the announcement, the Valleyfolk channel lost 20,000 subscribers and over 700 patrons, prompting a follow-up video from the trio apologizing for their handling of the announcement.<ref name=\"reveal_firing_cc\">{{cite web |last1=McCarthy |first1=Shawn L. |title=The Valleyfolk reveals they fired Lee Newton after winning NBC\u2019s Bring The Funny |url=https://thecomicscomic.com/2019/11/07/the-valleyfolk-reveals-they-fired-lee-newton-after-winning-nbcs-bring-the-funny/ |website=The Comic's Comic}}</ref>\n\n==Recurring segments==\n*Your Show - a variety show that often involves sketches, games, and viewer questions.<ref name=\"TubeFilterYourShow\">[https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/07/11/the-valleyfolk-variety-series-your-show/ The Valleyfolk, SourceFed\u2019s Spiritual Successor, Launches Variety Series Titled \u2018Your Show\u2019]</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=57gqeKoLMj0 Our Baby Is Born]</ref>\n*Your World Today - a satirical news and current events show.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXz9498yucsQmTyqtwQU2ps5GzQNg4guh Your World Today]</ref>\n*The Valleycast - a weekly behind the scenes video podcast.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXz9498yucsSQ8InQAUmC1W9vVGK3XFfO The Valleycast Highlights]</ref>\n*Games\n**Trivia Bidet\n**Movie Movie Game\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Bring the Funny}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Valleyfolk, The}}\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:American comedy troupes]]\n[[Category:American podcasters]]\n[[Category:American sketch comedians]]\n[[Category:Bring the Funny contestants]]\n[[Category:Comedians from California]]\n[[Category:Comedy YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Performing groups established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Sketch comedy troupes]]\n[[Category:SourceFed people]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2018]]\n", "name_user": "Patrickbensine", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Valleyfolk"}
{"title_page": "2002\u201303 Divizia B", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n | country            = {{ROU}}\n | competition        = [[Divizia B]]\n | season             = 2002\u201303\n | teams              = 32 (2x16)\n | promoted           = [[FC Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti|Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti]]<br>[[FC Unirea Alba Iulia|Apulum Alba Iulia]]<br>[[FC Bihor Oradea|FC Oradea]]\n | relegated          = [[CSM Suceava|Bucovina Suceava]]<br>[[CS Gilortul T\u00e2rgu C\u0103rbune\u0219ti|Gilortul T\u00e2rgu C\u0103rbune\u0219ti]]<br>[[Foresta F\u0103lticeni]]<br>[[CSP UM Timi\u0219oara|UM Timi\u0219oara]]\n | league topscorer   = [[Dan Codreanu]] (14 goals)\n | biggest home win   = \n | biggest away win   = \n | highest scoring    = \n | matches            = \n | total goals        = \n | longest wins       = \n | longest unbeaten   = \n | longest losses     = \n | highest attendance = \n | lowest attendance  = \n | average attendance = \n | prevseason = [[2001\u201302 Divizia B|2001\u201302]]\n | nextseason = [[2003\u201304 Divizia B|2003\u201304]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2002\u201303 Divizia B''' was the 63rd season of the second tier of the [[Romanian football league system]].\n\nThe format has been maintained to two series, each of them having 16 teams. At the end of the season, the winners of the series promoted to [[Liga I|Divizia A]] and the last two places from both series relegated to [[Liga III|Divizia C]]. A promotion play-off was played between the 13th and 14th-placed in the [[2002\u201303 Divizia A|Divizia A]] and the runners-up of the Divizia B series.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesr/roem2hist.html#96 rsssf.com]</ref><ref>[http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/divizia_b/tables/1995_96.shtml romaniansoccer.ro]</ref>\n\n== Team changes ==\n{{col-begin|width=auto}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===To Divizia B===\n'''Promoted from [[2001\u201302 Divizia C|Divizia C]]'''\n* [[FC Politehnica Ia\u0219i (1945)|Politehnica Unirea Ia\u0219i]]\n* [[FC Gloria Buz\u0103u|Gloria Buz\u0103u]]\n* [[CS Medgidia|Medgidia]]\n* [[CSM Alexandria|Rulmentul Alexandria]]\n* [[CS Gilortul T\u00e2rgu C\u0103rbune\u0219ti|Gilortul T\u00e2rgu C\u0103rbune\u0219ti]]\n* [[FC Corvinul Hunedoara|Corvinul Hunedoara]]\n* [[CFR Cluj]]\n* [[CSM Suceava|Bucovina Suceava]]**\n\n'''Relegated from [[2001\u201302 Divizia A|Divizia A]]'''\n* [[FC Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti|Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti]]\n* [[CSP UM Timi\u0219oara|UM Timi\u0219oara]]\n{{col-break|gap=5em}}\n\n===From Divizia B===\n'''Relegated to [[2002\u201303 Divizia C|Divizia C]]'''\n* [[Tractorul Bra\u0219ov]]\n* [[FCM C\u00e2mpina|Dinamo Poiana C\u00e2mpina]]\n* [[CSM Moine\u0219ti|Petrolul Moine\u0219ti]]\n* [[ASA T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219 (1962)|ASA T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219]]\n* [[CSM Roman (football)|Laminorul Roman]]\n* [[CSM Jiul Petro\u0219ani|Jiul Petro\u0219ani]]\n* [[AFC Rocar Bucure\u0219ti|Rocar Bucure\u0219ti]]\n* [[FC Politehnica Timi\u0219oara|Politehnica Timi\u0219oara]]**\n\n'''Promoted to [[2002\u201303 Divizia A|Divizia A]]'''\n* [[FC AEK Bucure\u0219ti|AEK Bucure\u0219ti]]**\n* [[FC UTA Arad|UTA Arad]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Other===\n''AEK Bucure\u0219ti'' merged with ''Politehnica Timi\u0219oara'' and was absorbed. Politehnica played directly in the first tier, instead of third and also was renamed as [[FC Politehnica Timi\u0219oara|Politehnica AEK Timi\u0219oara]].\n\n[[CSM Suceava|Bucovina Suceava]] break the alliance with [[Foresta F\u0103lticeni]], bought the place from [[Tractorul Bra\u0219ov]] and was enrolled directly in the second tier.\n\n[[FC Olimpia Satu Mare|Olimpia Satu Mare]] bought the place of Metrom Bra\u0219ov, which chose to sell it again, instead of playing at the second level.\n\n===Renamed teams===\n''Diplomatic Foc\u0219ani'' was renamed as [[CSM Foc\u0219ani|Unirea Foc\u0219ani]].\n\n''Foresta Suceava'' was moved back from [[Suceava]] to [[F\u0103lticeni]] and renamed as [[Foresta F\u0103lticeni]].\n\n''FC Bihor Oradea'' was renamed as [[FC Bihor Oradea|FC Oradea]].\n\n==League tables==\n=== Seria I ===\n{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|source=[http://www.romaniansoccer.ro/divizia_b/tables/2002_03.shtml romaniansoccer.ro] {{in lang|ro}}\n\n<!--Update team positions here-->\n|team1=PET |team2=GBZ |team3=ONE |team4=MID |team5=IAS |team6=ELE |team7=IGB |team8=DUB |team9=PLO |team10=FOC |team11=INT |team12=MED |team13=CIM |team14=BUC |team15=RUL |team16=FOR \n\n<!--Update team qualifications here (defined below)-->\n|result1=P |result2=PP \n|result6=I |result14=R |result15=S |result16=R \n\n<!--Team results here-->|update=30 June 2003\n|win_PET= 18|draw_PET=  7|loss_PET=  5|gf_PET= 42|ga_PET= 19 <!-- Petrolul Ploie\u0219ti -->\n|win_GBZ= 16|draw_GBZ=  7|loss_GBZ=  7|gf_GBZ= 44|ga_GBZ= 31 <!-- SGloria Buz\u0103u -->\n|win_ONE= 15|draw_ONE=  4|loss_ONE= 11|gf_ONE= 55|ga_ONE= 35 <!-- FC One\u0219ti -->\n|win_MID= 15|draw_MID=  4|loss_MID= 11|gf_MID= 45|ga_MID= 43 <!-- Midia N\u0103vodari -->\n|win_IAS= 13|draw_IAS=  7|loss_IAS= 10|gf_IAS= 41|ga_IAS= 32 <!-- Politehnica Ia\u0219i -->\n|win_ELE= 14|draw_ELE=  4|loss_ELE= 12|gf_ELE= 41|ga_ELE= 46 <!-- Electromagnetica Bucure\u0219ti -->\n|win_IGB= 11|draw_IGB=  9|loss_IGB= 10|gf_IGB= 37|ga_IGB= 31 <!-- Inter Gaz Bucure\u0219ti -->\n|win_DUB= 12|draw_DUB=  6|loss_DUB= 12|gf_DUB= 32|ga_DUB= 31 <!-- Dacia Unirea Br\u0103ila -->\n|win_PLO= 12|draw_PLO=  5|loss_PLO= 13|gf_PLO= 33|ga_PLO= 40 <!-- Metalul Plopeni -->\n|win_FOC= 12|draw_FOC=  5|loss_FOC= 13|gf_FOC= 34|ga_FOC= 35 <!-- Unirea Foc\u0219ani -->\n|win_INT= 12|draw_INT=  5|loss_INT= 13|gf_INT= 41|ga_INT= 32 <!-- Interna\u021bional Pite\u0219ti -->\n|win_MED= 11|draw_MED=  5|loss_MED= 14|gf_MED= 36|ga_MED= 41 <!-- Medgidia -->\n|win_CIM= 10|draw_CIM=  5|loss_CIM= 15|gf_CIM= 31|ga_CIM= 45 <!-- Cimentul Fieni -->\n|win_BUC=  9|draw_BUC=  7|loss_BUC= 14|gf_BUC= 25|ga_BUC= 38 <!-- Bucovina Suceava -->\n|win_RUL=  8|draw_RUL=  3|loss_RUL= 19|gf_RUL= 29|ga_RUL= 48 <!-- Rulmentul Alexandria -->\n|win_FOR=  7|draw_FOR=  5|loss_FOR= 18|gf_FOR= 26|ga_FOR= 51 