n==Divizia A play-off==\nThe 13th and 14th-placed teams of the [[2002\u201303 Divizia A|Divizia A]] faced the 2nd-placed teams of the Divizia B.\n\n{{TwoLegStart}}\n{{TwoLegResult|'''[[FC Politehnica Timi\u0219oara|Poli AEK Timi\u0219oara]]'''|| 8\u20134 |[[FC Gloria Buz\u0103u|Gloria Buz\u0103u]]|| 5\u20133 | 3\u20131}}\n{{TwoLegResult|[[ASC O\u021belul Gala\u021bi|O\u021belul Gala\u021bi]]|| 3\u20134 |'''[[FC Bihor Oradea|FC Oradea]]'''|| 2\u20131 | 1\u20133 {{aet}}}}\n|}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date= 14 June 2003\n|time= 18:00 [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]] ([[UTC+03:00|UTC+3]])\n|team1= [[FC Politehnica Timi\u0219oara|Poli AEK Timi\u0219oara]]\n|score= 5\u20133\n|report= https://www.romaniansoccer.ro/divizia_a/2002_03/play_off.shtml\n|team2= '''[[FC Gloria Buz\u0103u|Gloria Buz\u0103u]]'''\n|goals1= [[C\u0103lin Zanc|Zanc]] {{goal|28}}<br>[[Cristian Silv\u0103\u0219an|Silv\u0103\u0219an]] {{goal|54}}<br>[[Florin B\u0103tr\u00e2nu|B\u0103tr\u00e2nu]] {{goal|59}}<br>[[Ciprian Prodan|C.Prodan]] {{goal|71}}<br>[[Mircea Oprea|Oprea]] {{goal|90+3}}\n|goals2= [[Dumitru Gheorghe (footballer)|D.Gheorghe]] {{goal|13}}<br>[[Costel Petre|C.Petre]] {{goal|26}}<br>[[Iulian Apostol|Apostol]] {{goal|68}}\n|stadium= [[Stadionul Dan P\u0103ltini\u0219anu|Dan P\u0103ltini\u0219anu]]\n|location= [[Timi\u0219oara]]\n|attendance= 20,000\n|referee= Viorel Anghelinei ([[Gala\u021bi]])\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date= 14 June 2003\n|time= 18:00 [[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]] ([[UTC+03:00|UTC+3]])\n|team1= [[ASC O\u021belul Gala\u021bi|O\u021belul Gala\u021bi]]\n|score= 2\u20131\n|report= https://www.romaniansoccer.ro/divizia_a/2002_03/play_off.shtml\n|team2= '''[[FC Bihor Oradea|FC Oradea]]'''\n|goals1= [[Cornel Cornea|Cornea]] {{goal|28}}<br>[[Mihai Guri\u021b\u0103|Guri\u021b\u0103]] {{goal|67}}\n|goals2= [[Bogdan Vr\u0103jitoarea|Vr\u0103jitoarea]] {{goal|45|pen.}}\n|stadium= [[Stadionul O\u021belul|O\u021belul]]\n|location= [[Gala\u021bi]]\n|attendance= 7,00