{"title_page": "List of Manglerud Star Ishockey seasons", "text_new": "'''[[Manglerud Star Ishockey]]''' are a Norwegian [[ice hockey]] club based in [[Oslo]]. They are members of the highest Norwegian ice hockey league, [[GET-ligaen|Eliteserien]] (known as [[GET-ligaen]] for sponsorship reasons). Manglerud Star Ishockey are the ice hockey department of [[IL Manglerud Star]], a sports club founded in 1913. Originally known as Star, the club became known as Manglerud/Star after merging with Manglerud IL in 1964, and eventually Manglerud Star (without the [[Slash (punctuation)|slash]]).<ref name=\"history\">{{cite web |url=http://www.mshockey.no/sak/000150.asp |title=Manglerud Star 1913 |work=Manglerud Star Ishockey |accessdate=2010-04-14 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> Ice hockey was included as an activity in 1967,<ref name=\"info\">{{cite web |url=http://www.mshockey.no/sak/000027.asp |title=Klubbinfo, Historikk |work=Manglerud Star Ishockey |accessdate=2010-04-14 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> and is today one of two sports practised by the club, the other being [[association football|football]].<ref name=\"history\"/> As of [[2009-10 GET-ligaen season|2010]], they have completed twenty-nine seasons in the Eliteserien and have won 385 regular season games.\n\nManglerud Star achieved success in the early years of their existence thanks to a selection of talented young players who, after winning several youth and junior championships, brought the club into the highest division ahead of the 1973&ndash;74 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mshockey.no/sak/000029.asp |title=Da MS tok b\u00f8tta |work=Manglerud Star Ishockey |accessdate=2010-04-14 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> From then on and until the early 1980s, the club fought regularly for the League Championship, finishing the season as runners-up five times in a row from 1975 to 1979. In the playoffs, they were increasingly successful until finally winning back-to-back [[List of Norwegian ice hockey champions|Norwegian Championship]] titles in 1977 and 1978. After losing in the Finals against [[V\u00e5lerenga Ishockey|V\u00e5lerengen]] in 1982, a long period of decline ensued, culminating in relegation to the second level in the 1990&ndash;91 season. Having returned to the Eliteserien in 1993, Manglerud Star collaborated with [[Furuset Ishockey|Furuset]] and a group of investors to form the [[Spektrum Flyers]] franchise in 1994.<ref name=\"info\"/> When this effort collapsed after only two seasons, Manglerud Star chose to again compete as a team in their own right.\n\n==Seasons==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|bgcolor=\"#D0E7FF\"|<small>'''[[List of Norwegian ice hockey champions|Norwegian Champions]]'''</small>\n|bgcolor=\"#FFE6BD\"|<small>'''Regular Season Champions'''</small>\n|bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\"|<small>'''[[Promotion and relegation|Promoted]]'''</small>\n|bgcolor=\"#FFCCCC\"|<small>'''[[Promotion and relegation|Relegated]]'''</small>\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 95%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!rowspan=\"2\"|League\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Division\n!colspan=\"10\"|Regular season{{ref label|key|a|a}}\n!colspan=\"8\"|Postseason{{ref label|key|a|a}}\n|-\n!GP\n!W\n!L\n!T\n!OTW\n!OTL\n!GF\n!GA\n!Pts\n!Finish\n!GP\n!W\n!L\n!T\n!GF\n!GA\n!Pts\n!Result\n|-\n!1969\u201370\n|'''3. divisjon'''\n|bgcolor=\"#FFE6BD\"|'''B'''\n|10\n|9\n|1\n|0\n|&mdash;\n|&mdash;\n|46\n|20\n|18\n|bgcolor=\"#FFE6BD\"|'''1st'''\n|5\n|4\n|1\n|0\n|16\n|10\n|8\n|align=left bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\"|'''Won''' 3.&nbsp;divisjon Championship{{ref label|qualy70|b|b}}\n|-\n!1970\u201371\n|2. divisjon\n|A\n|10\n|5\n|2\n|3\n|&mdash;\n|&mdash;\n|41\n|31\n|13\n|2nd\n|6\n|2\n|3\n|1\n|15\n|29\n|5\n|align=left|3rd in Qualifying for 1.&nbsp;divisjon\n|-\n!1971\u201372\n|2. divisjon\n|A\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|&mdash;\n|&mdash;\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n!1972\u201373\n|2. divisjon\n|A\n|8\n|6\n|1\n|1\n|&mdash;\n|&mdash;\n|44\n|17\n|13\n|2nd\n|10\n|8\n|2\n|0\n|54\n|21\n|16\n|align=\"left\" bgcolor=\